title: Iran Sentences Five to Death Over Killing of Paramilitary Member
description: The unidentified defendants were convicted of involvement in the death of Ruhollah Ajamian, a member of the Basij paramilitary organization, who was killed last month.

title: As Israel's Left Suffers Defeat, So Does Two-State Solution
description: The ascendancy of ultranationalist and religious parties in Israel reflects a decline in support for a Jewish and Palestinian state side by side.

title: Hungary Blocks EU Plan to Raise Over $18 Billion in Funding for Ukraine
description: EU finance ministers failed to agree on providing vital economic assistance for Ukraine next year, with Hungary stymying for now efforts to secure the loan through common EU debt issuance.

title: Russian Oligarch Seizes 400,000 Acres of Ukrainian Farmland, Owners Say
description: The family company of a Putin ally and former Russian agriculture minister has become one of the biggest farm operators in Ukraine.

title: High Debt Levels Could Pressure Developing Countries, World Bank Says
description: Developing countries have amassed high levels of debt that could be difficult to repay as the global economy slows and interest rates rise, the bank said.

title: Indonesia Bans Sex Outside Marriage
description: Lawmakers appproved an overhaul of the criminal code empowering the state to punish people for offenses such as blasphemy and extramarital sex.

title: Moscow Says Ukrainian Drones Hit Third Russian Airfield in Two Days
description: The attack on the Kursk airport, which was closed to civil aviation after Russia invaded Ukraine in February, followed Monday’s strikes on Russian strategic-bomber bases in Engels and Diagilevo.

title: Putin Grips Economy Tighter to Supply Russian War Machine
description: Russia has commandeered private enterprise to keep the military armed in fight against Ukraine but faces labor and tech shortages.

title: China Sends Off Late Leader Jiang Zemin With Siren Blasts, Somber Memorial
description: Chinese authorities projected an air of national grief and unity as they tamped down rare dissent against the ruling Communist Party.

title: U.S., EU Agree to Coordinate Semiconductor Subsidy Programs
description: The two sides at a meeting make little progress over U.S. electric-car subsidies, an issue raised by the French president during his White House visit.
